    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Patricius" ref="#people/305">Landulfus</persName> divina ordinante
                        providencia, et <persName key="#Patricius" ref="#people/154"
                            >Atenulfus</persName> Longobardorum gentis antipatus <rs
                            key="#Patricius">patricius</rs> et patricius. Cum antipatricii
                        excellencia peticione dilecti sui, iuste petenti clementer favet. Quapropter
                        noverit omnium <rs key="#Assembly #fidelisOf">fidelium</rs> nostrorum
                        presencium scilicet ac futurorum sagacitas, <persName key="#Intercessory"
                                ><name ref="Maio">Maionem</name></persName> dilectissimum nostrum
                        obsecrasse nostram clemenciam, quatenus <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">concederemus</rs> in <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Mountains #Landed_possessions #Rivers" ref="#juridical_persons/1900"
                            >Beati Vincencii</orgName> levite, et martyris domini nostri Iesu
                        Christi, ubi statim <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1938"
                            >Godelpertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> regimen tenere videtur, quod edificatum est
                        super <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturni</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Rivers">fluminis</rs> fontem, omnes res et possessiones iam fati
                        cenobii, que esse videntur in <rs key="#Fines">finibus</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Rivers #Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Fines"
                            ref="#estates/1901">Benafranis</geogName>, sicuti per <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">precepta</rs> antecessorum
                        nostrorum, videlicet imperatorum, regum, et principum, ac ducum, nec non
                        offerciones, et scripciones quorumdam Deo devotorum concessas, et
                        confirmatas ante nos. Cuius peticioni ob reverenciam iam dicti abbatis,
                        omniumque venerabilum <rs key="#Monks">fratrum</rs>, qui in iam fato cenobio
                        degunt, libenter assensum prebuimus, rata et congrua nobis suggerentes, pro
                        salutis remedium anime nostre, hos nostre munificencie apices exinde fieri
                        iussimus, per quos omnino concedimus, et confirmamus, et perpetualiter
                        omnibus temporibus possidendum in iam fato monasterio Sancti Vincencii
                        Christi martyris ipsas res in prefato loco <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Churches" ref="#places/2300">Benafrano</placeName> per hos
                        videlicet fines incipiente a <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2323">Sangro</placeName>; inde per
                            <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#places/2814">montes puplicos</placeName>, usque in <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montem</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2324">Azze</placeName>, et sic revolvente monte eodem,
                        usque in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2327">Melfa</placeName>; et quemammodum decurrit ipsa
                        Melfa, usque ubi coniungit se cum parvo <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui
                        dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2813">Mellarinus</placeName>,
                        et ab hinc in vertice <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montis</rs>, qui dicitur Balbola, et sic per cilium eiusdem montis,
                        usque in montem Archanum, et <rs key="#Mountains">montem</rs> Marthe, <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montemque</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2325">Casale</placeName>, eosque videlicet montes
                        extrinsecus circumdantes, in ortum usque riaginis, qui nominatur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2309">Ravennola</placeName>; et a capite
                        eiusdem riaginis iuxta montes puplicos venientes, usque in <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2326">montem</placeName>, qui est super <placeName
                            key="#Cities" ref="#places/2300">Benafranam</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">urbem</rs>; eodem vero revolvente monte, usque in cilium
                        montis, qui est super <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs>, que vocatur
                            <geogName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1929">Arcora</geogName>, que est hereditas <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1904">Sancte Dei genitricis Marie</orgName>, que
                            <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#places/2330">Olivetum</placeName> vocatur, subiecta prefati
                        cenobii; et ecclesie similiter hereditas <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/1910">Sancte
                            Christine</orgName> cum inclitis <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terris</rs> suis, et cum reliquis finibus ipsa hereditas circumdata
                        usque in fluvio Vulturno; nam iterum ex alia parte incipiente a primo fine
                        per iam dicto fluvio Sangro, ipsoque relinquente fluvio quomodo decernit
                        apparu colle, et pergens usque in <rs key="#Rivers">rivum</rs>, qui dicitur
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2328">Foruli</placeName>; eodemque
                        decurrente rivio usque in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2329">Vantra</placeName>, et quomodo
                        decurrit ipsum flumen in alio flumine qui Vulturnus dicitur, et quemammodum
                        decurrit ipsum flumen iuxta terras eiusdem monasterii usque in predictis
                        finibus et terris ecclesie Sancte Marie, insuper concedimus et confirmamus
                        in prefato cenobio omnia <rs key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma"
                            >precepta</rs> antecessorum nostrorum, videlicet Karoli, Ludovici, atque
                        Lotharii, ducum, et principum, seu omnes legales scripciones, eo scilicet
                        ordine hec omnia in prefato monasterio concedimus, quo superius legitur,
                        habendi et possidendi sine ullius comitis, castaldei vel iudicis, aut
                        cuiuscumque magne seu parve persone contradiccione, vel inquietudine, sed
                        quieto ordine habeat, et possideat omnia, que prelegitur, iam dictum
                        monasterium in eo ordine, sicut superius legitur in perpetuum nullo
                        aliquando contrario ingerente. Ut autem hec nostra concessio et confirmacio
                        ab omnibus verius observetur, manu propria scripsimus, et anulo nostro
                        subter iussimus sigillari. <date>Data .VI°. idus iulias, anno .XVI°.
                            principatus domni Landulfi, et .VII°. anno principatus domni Atenulfi,
                            indiccione .IIII.a. Actum in <placeName key="#Assembly #fidelisOf #Patricius" ref="#places/173"
                                >Capua</placeName></date>.</ab>
                </div>
